You cannot have a class with @State property, @State are meant for structs that conform to View protocol.
For classes you use ObservableObject protocol and bind to them by using @ObservedObject.
Also let the compiler generate an initialiser for you:

    struct Junk_Test: View {
        
        @ObservedObject var model: JunkModel
        
        var body: some View {
            Text(model.junk)
        }
    }
    
    
    class JunkModel: ObservableObject {
        var junk: String = &quot;xyz&quot;
    }
    
    
    struct Junk_Test_Previews: PreviewProvider {
    
        @State static var model = JunkModel()
    
        static var previews: some View {
            Junk_Test(model: model)
        }
    }

